replies.commentText: Hi Nikhil, There is no such thing as ‘how many languages you should learn?’ because all depends on what you want to build, where you’re coming from and why you got involved in machine learning. But in any case, the most important programming languages for Machine Learning are Java, R language,  C Language and Python.

When you use 'regr.fit(size2,house_price), should all data be in this format? Also what should you do about adding multplie data sets? Thank you for your help

replies.commentText:
Hi Moody, thanks for the appreciation, we are glad you liked our video. Here is the answer to your questions:1. Size 2 is the name of the variable we have used
2. Yes, while fitting a model the data format for the variables(size2,house_price) should be same
3. pd.merge function is used to combine multiple data sets
Hope that answers your query. Feel free to reach out for any further doubts. 


Happy learning from Simplilearn team!
